---
// Hub route stub. One of these per hub, deliberately, rather than a shared dynamic route.
//
// The `hubs` collection cannot be folded into src/pages/[slug]/index.astro: putting
// CourseLayout and HubLayout behind one page file pulls both layouts' component graphs
// into the same Rollup entry, which is how commit 1c75bb2 leaked BundleOffer's and
// ProcessTrack's scoped stylesheets onto every course page. That was reverted. Only six
// components in this repo carry scoped <style> blocks, and those two are among them, so
// the leak is a real hazard rather than a theoretical one.
//
// A per-hub stub keeps each layout in its own module graph. It also costs nothing at the
// URL level: static routes outrank dynamic ones in Astro, and [slug]'s getStaticPaths only
// ever emits the four course ids, so there is no collision. /cpd and /cpd-tas already prove
// the pattern.
//
// The trade-off is that a hub MDX with no stub renders silently nowhere. The guardrails
// bijection assert (A2) is what closes that hole - do not add a hub without it.
import { getEntry, render } from 'astro:content';
import HubLayout from '../layouts/HubLayout.astro';

const entry = await getEntry('hubs', 'owner-builder-courses');
if (!entry) throw new Error('hubs/owner-builder-courses.mdx is missing; /owner-builder-courses cannot render.');
const { Content } = await render(entry);
---
<HubLayout hub={entry.data}>
  <Content />
</HubLayout>
